# Citation metadata. Mirrors the BibTeX block in README.md ("How to cite");
# edits here must be mirrored there.
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
type: software
title: "Slow Wave: a mechanism-decomposed test bench for sleep-inspired memory consolidation in continual-learning LLM agents"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-12
license: Apache-2.0
url: "https://github.com/JusHoya/slow_wave"
repository-code: "https://github.com/JusHoya/slow_wave"
abstract: >-
  A reproducible research test bench for sleep-inspired memory consolidation
  in frozen-weights LLM agents: a synthetic continual task stream with
  ground-truth relevance labels, a dual-store (episodic/semantic/archival)
  memory substrate, a four-operator dream engine (replay, transfer, downscale,
  generative-augment), and a nine-arm preregistered control battery whose
  every figure and number regenerates from committed data in one command.
authors:
  - family-names: Hoyer
    given-names: Melvin
    name-suffix: III
keywords:
  - memory consolidation
  - continual learning
  - LLM agents
  - sleep
  - experience replay
  - catastrophic forgetting
  - preregistration
  - reproducibility
